Rupert Murdoch â€™s  News Corp. (NWSA)  has
raised its stake in Rotana, the media company controlled by
Saudi billionaire Prince Alwaleed bin Talal, to 18.97 percent
from 14.53 percent,  The National  reported, citing an
unidentified spokeswoman.  News Corp. increased its stake in Rotana, which runs
several television and radio stations, by exercising the
remaining half of an option to buy new shares issued by Rotana
for $35 million, the Abu Dhabi-based newspaper said, citing the
